msgid "Parameter estimates from the mediation model, organized by direct effects, indirect effects, and total effects."
msgstr ""

msgid "Direct effects"
msgstr ""

msgid "Direct effects of predictors on outcomes, bypassing all mediators (the c or c' path). A significant direct effect indicates that the predictor influences the outcome independently of the mediation pathway."
msgstr ""

msgid "Indirect effects"
msgstr ""

msgid "Indirect effects of predictors on outcomes transmitted through mediators. Each indirect effect is the product of the path coefficients along the mediation pathway (a × b). A significant indirect effect indicates that mediation occurs through that pathway."
msgstr ""

msgid "Total Effects"
msgstr ""

msgid "Total effects combining the direct effect and all indirect effects for each predictor-outcome pair. The total effect equals the sum of the direct and indirect effects (c = c' + a × b)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Total indirect effects"
msgstr ""

msgid "Total indirect effects summed across all mediators for each predictor-outcome pair. When there are multiple mediators, this gives the combined strength of all indirect pathways."
msgstr ""

msgid "Residual covariances"
msgstr ""

msgid "Estimated residual covariances between endogenous variables (mediators and outcomes). These represent shared variance not accounted for by the model's directed paths."
msgstr ""

msgid "Path coefficients"
msgstr ""

msgid "Individual path coefficients in the mediation model. These include the a paths (predictor to mediator) and b paths (mediator to outcome), which constitute the building blocks of indirect effects."
msgstr ""

msgid "Estimator is %s."
msgstr ""

